Karabiner:
Config in configs directory. Summary:
- caps -> esc
- caps+x -> ctrl+opt+cmd+x
- Remap caps to esc by self and super if in combination  for all keyboards.
  http://brettterpstra.com/2017/06/15/a-hyper-key-with-karabiner-elements-full-instructions/
- Swap fn and left_control for the "Apple Internal Keyboard / Trackpad". Need to keep a fn so I can use it for fn+hjkl as arrows.

Slate:
https://github.com/jigish/slate
Using super (cmd+ctrl+opt) and adding shift to it sometimes.

Brew install
tmux
reattach-to-user-namespace (or else tmux will crash with my tmux.conf)

Crontab for Downloads:
*/15 * * * * find /Users/rpt/Downloads/ -mtime +14 -maxdepth 1 -exec mv {} /tmp \;


iTerm2:
Download it from website
Go to Settings > Preferences
Set the load preferences from custom folder and set it to dotfiles/configs (where com.googlecode.iterm2.plist should
be)

For font, go to https://github.com/source-foundry/Hack and download + install.

Colourschemes for iTerm2 (might not be needed if above is done):
https://github.com/altercation/solarized/tree/master/iterm2-colors-solarized

Vim:
You'll want to `brew install vim` instead of the provided one with macos as it's missing some features.
